Title: 1 week and issue still unresolved with my order
Content: I contacted customer service over a week ago because the website had a bug in which I couldn‚Äôt input my billing address that was different from the shipping address (I never had an issue with this in the past).We have gone back and forth with over 18 emails. I have sent screenshots, Loom video recordings, tried on multiple browsers and devices. This was for a gift that I spent at least 4 hours on and I have 3 other projects that I had been planning no ordering as well. Where are we now?1) The individual who has been answering my inquiries has asked me 4 times for the same video recording‚Ä¶ which I‚Äôm happy to do if there is ever a solution. 2) I was told to send a video recording of me inputting my credit card info and trying to validate with the wrong billing address. I told him I wouldn‚Äôt do it because he shouldn‚Äôt be asking for private information AND that my bank would shut off my card (like they did in the first place when I hadn‚Äôt caught the error).3) I was asked to try on the app. When I said I couldn‚Äôt see any of my drafts or project in the cart, I was told the app and the website don‚Äôt sync. He then ‚Äúinvited me to start a new project‚Äù.4) I was invited to do the project on the app even after I told him I don‚Äôt do projects on the app anymore after I lost several projects I had done on the app (so, a lot of time lost). When I reached out to CS that time, they basically just said they had problems with the app and to use the website.5) I have asked for this to be escalated to a supervisor multiple times, but have yet to speak to a supervisor.Honestly, I loved this company before. I‚Äôve done several photo books, prints for family, magnets, and had been planning to do photo book projects that would have easily cost me over ‚Ç¨1,000 euros when it‚Äôs all done. Now, I couldn‚Äôt do any of that even if I wanted. The quality of the photos are good, but their engineering team and customer service are so awful that I doubt I will return as a customer. I simply don‚Äôt have that much time to waste.

The customer service was very kind and they send me my prints one more time. So i am recommending them!

Title: Take your money without telling you
Content: I have used Cheerz for years, there magnets are lovley and good quality. Until they started forcing people to use the app to order! Last year i attempted an order on the app, it just wouldnt work, a number of times i tried checking out but it just kept asking me to add more pictures, i gave up in the end deleted the app and that was the end of it. A couple of days ago i attempted it again, the website sent me through to the app, but this time i could upload my pictures, added what i needed and checked out for ¬£17...fantastic! THEN i received an email confirmation for ¬£47!!! I checked my bank and there was a transaction for ¬£47!! I contacted them immediately!! The emails i have recieved so far have been appalling, each one not taking responsibility for whats happened and the go to copy and paste of terms and conditions is just sent to me advising why thwy cant refund. Today i received an email advising they can see i had the old version of the app and thats how old orders were added to my basket without me seeing them, and they would offer me an instore credit valid for 1 month!? Bear in mind this credit is for ¬£32 and there is NO WAY i will spend ¬£32 on magnets (thats all i buy) in 1 month, especially as were in the middle of a pandemic so we havent even been anywhere for any pictures to be worth making into magnets! So after explaining this they then offer me 3 months extension on this, i jave advised them i am still not happy and waiting on a reply but im not holding my breath. DO NOT USE THIS COMPANY UNLESS YOU ARE HAPPY THEM TAKING MOMEY WITHOUT ASKING YOU.**Update: After 2 long weeks of emails back and forth and i contacted the founder from the spanish branch on LinkedIn and another founder on Instagram (not sure if that had anything to do with it) but another colleague has been in touch and accepted my request to be refunded. I have had a confirmation email to advise my money will be back in my account shortly.

Title: This is going to be a positive review... maybe not
Content: I was hoping to write a positive review but this isn‚Äôt it. Fell foul of a discount scam which then cost me money but that‚Äôs not the problem or reason for the bad rating. My order was placed over a year ago but for some unknown never arrived. I did contact Cheerz support after approx a week but due to my email account being hacked I wasn‚Äôt able to provide an order reference and the customer service rep couldn‚Äôt find the order on my delivery address or name.Time rolls by and I‚Äôm able to access my email account again and whilst tidying up my historical emails I see an email from Cheerz asking for feedback so I completed it. Then their customer service team contact me, to offer some service recovery and they confirm now that they have the order ref, they can find and confirm my name and delivery address (which didn‚Äôt apparently exist previously).Cut a long story short, one of the customer service team tell me that they will reprint the order and post them out shortly to the original address. This sounds positive but stick with me, now as the original order is over a year ago, I‚Äôm now a little concerned that they would still have the images of my daughter so I queried this. This then prompted a very short email from another customer service rep, telling me that they had made a mistake and hadn‚Äôt realised that the order was over a year old and as the complaint was outside of their fifteen day cut off they couldn‚Äôt confirm my details and could do nothing for me. So in essence, when querying the missing order with fifteen days of the order I was advised they couldn‚Äôt find it.Then over a year later they actually confirm the details back to me.Then when asked how they can reprint the order, they say that it‚Äôs outside of the fifteen day complaint period, they state that they can‚Äôt confirm my details. All in all very weird, I‚Äôm not too sure they understand consumer rights and their systems to lose and find orders at will. Thankfully the order only cost me a few pounds due to the discount code but the customer service experience is at best obstructive and worst laughable with apparent breaches of GDPR data management.I won‚Äôt be using again and have asked that they remove my details from the system (assuming they can find them again) and not sell them to any third parties.
